# PPE burst mode (adaptive)

**Canon:** [`WORKFLOW_EFFICIENCY_OPERATOR_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/WORKFLOW_EFFICIENCY_OPERATOR_V1.md) · [`ppe-operator.mdc`](ppe-operator.mdc)

Operator `what's next?` runs burst per `BURST_PLAN.json` until cap or stop. Charter/explore/neutral: [`ppe-roles.mdc`](ppe-roles.mdc).

## Start

```bat
python scripts/ppe_burst_plan.py --write --json
```

| Verdict | Burst path |
|---------|------------|
| `IDE_BUILD` · `RUN_LOCAL` | `@ppe-director` → build/finish workers only |
| `FIX_PLAN` · `STALE_STATE` · `ERROR` | `@ppe-director` → one triage worker max |
| `RUN_AUTO` · `SUPPLY_LOW` | No burst |

## Stop when

- `workers_run >= max_cycles` or ESCALATE band
- Verdict `RUN_AUTO` or same stuck verdict twice
- Desktop relay guard blocks VM-only cmds

## Forbidden

- Implementing `IDE_BUILD` in the operator thread during burst
- `run_ppe_auto_local_loop.cmd` on desktop
